item.title: [AMQ-2512] "Failed to page in more queue messages"
item.description:

comments.comment: code inspection may get to the bottom of this but a test case would help. Can you attach your test code or describe what consumers and producers are present at the time?
My test client code attached. Starting from 30000-50000 messages delivery is much slower. Above situation usually happens at the end of processing (between 80 000 and 100 000 message received).

Full log file attached. Could it happened because of enableJournalDiskSyncs="false" setting?

One more observation: using different type of cursor than store based (which is default I guess) seems to improve dispatch behavior - no more exceptions, hangs and slow downs.

<pendingQueuePolicy>
<fileQueueCursor/>
</pendingQueuePolicy>

However I think store based cursor should also work fine and that's why I'm leaving this issue still open.

I have a test case that failed - but have made some improvements - plus reduced prefetch to 10 for consumers - would like verification if this is still an issue on the next 5.4-SNAPSHOT build - anyone ?
